         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">14/2/96 ¶  ¶ Some weeks ago, dear Dr Ramsay, I learnt to my great joy, from Mr Frogatt, ¶  that your health had greatly improved, so that you could feel renewed delight in science work as in days gone...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.02.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS 2278, Add on 706 1(1), Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS inserted in an extra-print copy of B96.03.03, inscribed: 'To Dr. Edw. Ramsay | FLS. FRSE., FGS. | CF. Z S. regardfully | offered by Ferd. von Mueller'.</p>
               </note>14/2/96</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Some weeks ago, dear Dr Ramsay, I learnt to my great joy, from Mr Frogatt,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is not known when, nor for how long, Walter Froggatt was in Melbourne.</p>
               </note> that your health had greatly improved, so that you could feel renewed delight in science work as in days gone bye.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The conversation turned also to the rare <name key="Claudea%20Bennettiana">Claudea Bennettiana</name> at the entrance of the Paramatta River,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Parramatta River, at the head of Sydney Harbour.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and the tantalizing desire since more than 40 years to learn what is the structure of the fruit. As you have probably time, have young helpmates, know the precise locality, could get the loan of the dredging apparatus from the museum, and I would pay for the boat hire, will you have kindly an other chase for it? Other wise I may not live to see the fruit, as my earthly career must necessarily soon draw to a close, considering that I commenced my researches in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">1839</hi>
               </seg>!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Very glad, to hear of you any how, I remain regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">if <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg> find fruiting specimens I shall of course mention publicly that you obtained them<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>M had been pressing Ramsay to collect specimens of this seaweed that included fruiting bodies since 1882; see M to E. Ramsay, 22 September 1882 (in this edition as 82-09-22c).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Claudea%20Bennettiana">Claudea Bennettiana</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
